        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Toronto 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May 1889<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/>
                Rev Dr <sic>Morrais</sic>&#33;<lb/>
                My dear Sir and Friend&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping you and your dear Lady<lb/> and family all are in best health<lb/> the same thank God I can assure<lb/> you from us.  Rev and dear Sir&#33;<lb/> I take very great pleasure to invite<lb/> you to the &#91;Hebrew&#93; of my youngest son<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; who is going to read his &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> and &#91;Hebrew&#93; also an <sic>adress</sic> to the &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> it will take place on &#91;Hebrew&#93; 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> June<lb/> It would afford me the <hi rend="underline">greatest</hi><lb/> pleasure if possible that you could<lb/> have had <hi rend="underline">favoured</hi> us with your<lb/> <hi rend="underline">presence</hi>.  Hoping these lines will<lb/> meet you all in good health<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>as it leaves us the weather<lb/> is very cool here especially in the<lb/> evenings&#44; but in winter it is as<lb/> cold pretty much like Russia&#45;&#45;<lb/> my Congregation here is getting on<lb/> slow but <hi rend="underline">safe</hi>&#61;my <sic>sallary</sic> thank<lb/> <hi rend="underline">God</hi> is <hi rend="underline">not too</hi> much&#45;&#45;But still<lb/> I have to <hi rend="underline">manage</hi> to get along&#44; it is<lb/> now nearly six years I am with them<lb/> and there is &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr A Marcus sends me very<lb/> often some <hi rend="underline">news</hi> about his &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> he seems to <hi rend="underline">improve</hi> in them<lb/> If ever you should see Mr M. J.<lb/> Potsdamer in your city please give<lb/> my kind regards to him &#38; family<lb/> excuse me troubling you&#45;&#45;<lb/> no more news at present<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the <sic>wheather</sic> is very cool here to<lb/> day.  I shall be very proud and<lb/> happy to hear from you soon<lb/> and wishing you from my <sic>verry</sic><lb/> heart &#91;Hebrew&#93; and<lb/> all good wishes&#44; and with best regards<lb/> to yourself and dear family and<lb/> friends I remain yours very truly<lb/> and Respectfully<lb/> Rev&#58; H Phillips<lb/></p>
            <p>Holy <sic>Blosoms</sic> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> 31 Richmond St East<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>To the Rev Dr <sic>Morrais</sic><lb/>
                Minister of the Portuguese<lb/>
                Congregation<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pens<lb/>
                U. S. A.<lb/></p>
            
            <p>not 367<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; 546 N. 5th 16 D 5<lb/>29&#93;<lb/></p>
